    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting a collector-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, a pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering. This example features the iconic 13B-REW rotary engine with its sophisticated sequential twin-turbocharger system, delivering seamless boost across the rev range. The powerplant is paired with a precise five-speed manual gearbox and a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. The chassis remains taut, utilizing its original four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and achieving an ideal 50/50 weight distribution. This specimen is in concours-level condition; the apex seals maintain high compression, and the complex vacuum system has been meticulously preserved to factory specifications. Finished in its original paint with a pristine interior, this RX-7 represents a rare opportunity to own a mechanically synchronized and aesthetically flawless rotary masterpiece.",
